Steno dictionary source for a Plover JS/TS snippet plugin, parsed by `src/parse.ts`. This is the authoritative data file — `snippets.txt` is a human-readable companion, not a build input.

Entries are fenced blocks: ` ````STROKE ... ```` ` with the stroke(s) on the open-fence line and the literal template body between fences. Optional `###Name` line above an entry names it; `@directives` below an entry (before the next entry) attach to it. Recognized directives: `@count KEYS` (bank of keys, e.g. `AOE`, that select an arity/count for `%d`/`%[...%]`), `@arity N` (generic type-argument slots required before a type stroke becomes terminal), `@multiline`, `@fuse` (merges a following type stroke's return type into the shape rather than requiring an intermediate untyped stroke), `@type` (marks an entry as a suffix-only type-emitter, invalid standalone), `@noarg` (type takes no generic args even if arity-capable elsewhere), `@literal` (emit body verbatim, no template operator expansion — used by the big data-structure blocks at the bottom).

Template operators consumed by the parser: `%0`-`%9` landing/tabstop points (`%0` is the plain-profile landing), `%d` literal digit for the in-scope count (total count outside a `%[...%]` repeat, iteration index inside one), `%t` type-slot filled by an appended type stroke, `%b` body-break (toggles one-liner vs block form for a whole translation — all `%b` in one template flip together), `%p` pattern-slot, `%[sep|body%]` repeat construct (sep never trails the last item), `%(EXPR)` computed landing point linear in `d`, and escapes `\n \t \{ \} \% \| \\ \``.

Structurally the file is organized into sections by comment headers: functions (`STKWR-PBGS` root, many suffixes), params, if/else-if/else, ternary, for/while/do-while loops, try/catch/finally, switch/case, declarations, console.log/throw, classes, destructuring, arrays/index, a large callback-method-root family (`STKWR*PLT` root: array/string/Math methods via chorded suffixes), a block of standalone type strokes (each `@type`, some `@arity`/`@noarg`), a standalone type-emitter stroke `STKWR-T` that takes any following type as a suffix, two large literal custom-function snippets (fibonacci, quicksort/quickselect sharing a `partition` helper — note both quicksort and quickselect entries redeclare `partition`, so pasting both in the same file causes a duplicate-declaration error), and a data-structures section (`STKWR-RBGT` root) emitting complete generic TS classes (LinkedList, DoublyLinkedList, Stack, Queue, Deque, MinHeap, MaxHeap, BinaryTree, BST, Graph, Trie) verbatim via `@literal`.

Anyone editing `src/parse.ts`'s operator handling, count-bank logic, or fuse/arity resolution must keep this file's directive semantics in sync — it's the sole source of truth for stroke-to-template mappings; there's no separate schema file.